annotations:
I need a sense of urgency that I hope you’ve got
 For you to call me back even when I tell you not to
She’s jaded from past relationships, acting as if she doesn’t want another. She wants someone to see through her actions, understand, and fight for a relationship.

Got too many holes where lovers used to be
 Can’t be good for me, but I don’t like to be alone, really
She’s conflicted because she’s tired of getting hurt in relationships, but she doesn’t want to be alone.

The worst thing you could do is leave, when I tell you, “Just go”
 We both know I don’t want you to leave me alone
 The worst thing you could do is leave, when I tell you, “Just go”
 Don’t listen to me, don’t listen to me, no
There’s a difference between her words and her thoughts. She probably says just go because she’s hurt, but she wants the other person to understand that she wants their help.

description.plain:
There have been many times when I’ve been so afraid to uproot my life in some way but just as afraid of what will happen if I don’t. This song is a conversation with myself about avoidance, denial, being afraid of change, and being afraid of stagnating. I shot the video in Los Angeles with Allyson from Pear Juice and a cast and crew of all women (besides our amazing producer Al!). Shooting the video was like being at summer camp – it was one of the best experiences and I’m so proud of how it turned out.

—Kate Bollinger, via Stereogum
